{
    "componentChunkName": "component---src-templates-blog-post-js",
    "path": "/Face-Spoofing-2D-Detection-Based-on-Moiré-Pattern-Analysis/",
    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Xiwen's Digital Garden"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"69e7100e-7b2e-56f8-b904-0080c6668055","excerpt":"Authors: Diogo C. Garcia, Ricardo L. de Queiroz Published In: IEEE Transactions on Information Forensics and Security - April 2015 DOI/ISBN: 10.1109/TIFS.201…","html":"<p><strong>Authors</strong>: Diogo C. Garcia, Ricardo L. de Queiroz</p>\n<p><strong>Published In</strong>: IEEE Transactions on Information Forensics and Security - April 2015</p>\n<p><strong>DOI/ISBN</strong>: 10.1109/TIFS.2015.2411394</p>\n<p><strong>Personal Note</strong>: prerequisites are Fourier analysis, undersampling, thresholding, and some statistics</p>\n<h2>1. Abstract</h2>\n<h3>What do we already know?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Face spoofing detection by combining image-quality analysis, motion analysis, texture analysis.</li>\n<li>Related work: detect printed and displayed face-spoofing images by using a support vector machine (SVM) to search for a lack of high-frequency information (Zhang et. al.)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>What do we want to solve?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Video replay attack: attackers show a copy of your face from video calls / recorded videos to bypass authentication.</li>\n<li>We want a theoretical model that works on any data.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How did the author(s) solve that problem?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Face spoofing detection by searching for Moiré patterns.</li>\n<li>Assumptions:\n<ul>\n<li>The face image to be checked is on a digital screen.</li>\n<li>Real images contain most of their energy at the low frequencies in the frequency domain.</li>\n<li>Face-spoofing images contain unusual peaks at high frequencies in the frequency domain.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Modelling:\n<ul>\n<li>Let <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N_1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N_2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> be the pixel lengths of a feature on the face image screen and on the face detection camera.</li>\n<li>When a camera captures a digital screen, their digital grids will overlap</li>\n<li>When the sampling frequency of the camera is larger than that of the face image screen, this overlap will cause Moiré patterns to occur (wave interference).</li>\n<li>Thus, for Moiré patterns to emerge in face-spoofing images: <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>></mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N_2/N_1>1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Differences from Zhang et. al.:\n<ul>\n<li>Zhang et. al. assumes that face-spoofing images contain fewer high-frequency content; whereas the authors search for distinct patterns that are high-pass in nature.</li>\n<li>The author use Difference-of-Gaussian filters to isolate high-frequency patterns in the frequency domain.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>What did the author(s) find?</h3>\n<p>An algorithm that detects face spoofing by finding high frequency peaks other than the baseband. (Baseband signal := information signals at their original frequencies)</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c3eb3ea312c66a4b7399b8e1c278205b/c83ae/flowchart.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.39240506329114%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Untitled\"\n        title=\"Flowchart taken from the paper\"\n        src=\"/static/c3eb3ea312c66a4b7399b8e1c278205b/f058b/flowchart.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c3eb3ea312c66a4b7399b8e1c278205b/c26ae/flowchart.png 158w,\n/static/c3eb3ea312c66a4b7399b8e1c278205b/6bdcf/flowchart.png 315w,\n/static/c3eb3ea312c66a4b7399b8e1c278205b/f058b/flowchart.png 630w,\n/static/c3eb3ea312c66a4b7399b8e1c278205b/40601/flowchart.png 945w,\n/static/c3eb3ea312c66a4b7399b8e1c278205b/c83ae/flowchart.png 1180w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Flowchart taken from the paper</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2>2. Contents</h2>\n<h3>Band-pass filtering</h3>\n<p>Ignore baseband signal so that the algorithm search for peaks at other frequency bands.\nConvolve the image <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span></span></span></span></span> with a Difference-of-Gaussians (DoG) filter <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">D</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>σ</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{D}(\\sigma,k)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">D</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> to get a band-pass filtered image <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}_{BP}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8361em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">BP</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">D</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>σ</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">G</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><msup><mi>σ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>−</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">G</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>σ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{D}(\\sigma,k)=\\mathbf{G}(0,\\sigma^2)-\\mathbf{G}(0,k\\sigma^2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">D</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1141em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">G</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8641em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1141em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">G</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8641em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>where <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">G</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>σ</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{G}(\\sigma,k)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">G</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> is a 2D-Gaussian function. <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span></span> define the center and width of the frequency band. Repeat the above steps by varying <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span></span></span></span></span> from <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>σ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma_0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.5806em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0359em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> to <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>σ</mi><mi>max</mi><mo>⁡</mo></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma_{\\max}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.5806em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0359em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mop mtight\"><span class=\"mtight\">m</span><span class=\"mtight\">a</span><span class=\"mtight\">x</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> in increments of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Delta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Δ</span></span></span></span></span> to get multiple <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}_{BP}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8361em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">BP</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<h3>Peak detection</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Perform maximum-correlation thresholding: given input image <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span></span></span></span></span>, we must find a threshold <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6151em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span></span></span></span></span> to create a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thresholding_(image_processing)\">binary image</a> <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>τ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\tau(\\mathbf{I})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> such that the correlation coefficient <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\rho</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ρ</span></span></span></span></span> between <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>τ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\tau(\\mathbf{I})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span></span></span></span></span> is maximized.</li>\n<li>The calculation for correlation coefficient is in the paper, it uses grey levels, frequency of occurrence of grey level, above and below threshold means</li>\n<li>After <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6151em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span></span></span></span></span> is found, use it to threshold the frequency domain of the band-pass filtered image <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">|\\mathscr{F}\\{\\mathbf{\\mathbf{I}}_{BP}\\}|</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.13634em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">BP</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span></span></span></span></span> of size <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>W</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">W\\times L</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">W</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span></span></span></span></span>.</li>\n<li>Then, count the percentage of pixels <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span></span> with values above <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6151em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span></span></span></span></span> (high frequency peaks).</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>W</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><munderover><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>W</mi></munderover><munderover><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>L</mi></munderover><mi>τ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p=\\frac{1}{WL}\\sum_{u=1}^W\\sum_{v=1}^L\\tau\\{|\\mathscr{F}\\{\\mathbf{\\mathbf{I}}_{BP}\\}|\\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:3.0954em;vertical-align:-1.2671em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.3214em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">W</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.8283em;\"><span style=\"top:-1.8829em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">u</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">=</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop op-symbol large-op\">∑</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-4.3em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">W</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.2671em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.8283em;\"><span style=\"top:-1.8829em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">=</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop op-symbol large-op\">∑</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-4.3em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.05em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">L</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.2671em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.13634em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">BP</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>If <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>&#x3C;</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mi>min</mi><mo>⁡</mo></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p&#x3C;p_{\\min}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3175em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mop mtight\"><span class=\"mtight\">m</span><span class=\"mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mtight\">n</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> (self defined), repeat step 1 with the next image <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">I</mi><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{I}_{BP}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8361em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">I</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">BP</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> with increased <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span></span></span></span></span>; Otherwise, it is a face-spoofing image.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Performance evaluation</h3>\n<p>The algorithm is tested with frontal pose images from the MITCBCL Face Recognition Database, the Extended Yale Face Database B and the Frontal face dataset from the Computational Group at Caltech.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Perfect detection for pixel ratio <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>≥</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N_2/N_1\\geq 2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span></span></span>, but for <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#x3C;</mo><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#x3C;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1&#x3C;N_2/N_1&#x3C;2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6835em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span></span></span>, perfect detection is not guaranteed.</li>\n<li>False living rate := percentage of spoofing images that are not detected</li>\n<li>False spoofing rate := percentage of real images that are detected as spoofing images</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>Results indicate that, in terms of false living rate, the proposed algorithm is outperformed for low pixel ratio values <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>≈</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(PR\\approx 1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">PR</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>, but Zhang et. al.’s algorithm cannot guarantee a null false living rate without sacrificing the false spoofing rate.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>Zhang et. al.’s algorithm also does not guarantee a null false spoofing rate, as opposed to the proposed algorithm.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>3. Conclusion</h2>\n<h3>Overall summary</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>New algorithm for detecting face-spoofing in video replay attacks</li>\n<li>Face-spoofing image on a digital screen → Moiré-Pattern → peaks of high frequencies detected.</li>\n<li>Real faces not on a screen → no Moiré-Patterns → mostly low frequencies → pass the check.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Limitations</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>This algorithm only works for faces on a digital screen. Attackers can bypass this by printing your face on a paper / using a 3D mask of your face.</li>\n<li>Has a maximum distance requirement <a href=\"#performance-evaluation\">(see 2.3)</a>.</li>\n<li>Has a minimum resolution requirement for the camera.</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Face-Spoofing 2D-Detection Based on Moiré Pattern Analysis","date":"October 16, 2021","description":"The authors introduce an algorithm to counter against video replay attacks by checking for Moiré patterns in the spoofed face image."}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/Seam-Carving-for-Content-Aware-Image-Resizing/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Seam Carving for Content-Aware Image Resizing"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/ATP-In-network-Aggregation-for-Multi-tenant-Learning/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ATP: In-network Aggregation for Multi-tenant Learning"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"69e7100e-7b2e-56f8-b904-0080c6668055","previousPostId":"0174c754-49d8-5774-8323-b6e6fd2ae3ab","nextPostId":"12d81589-7d7c-59b6-981b-c8e45c4619c9"}},
